{:experiment/type :prompt-ab,
 :experiment/verdict
 "H1 FALSIFIED for exhaustion; the bounded lens WINS on quality/brevity (2026-07-17, :local qwen36-35b-a3b + :gemma4 gemma-4-31b-it, thinking-ON, the FIRST genuine cross-family lens test). 16 cells (4 REAL stress-session turns × 2 conditions × 2 families). TWO SEPARABLE FINDINGS:\n  (1) THE EXHAUSTION IS OPERATIONAL, NOT PROMPT-LEVEL — H1 falsified. :bounded and :values BOTH exhaust on the SAME 2 dense multi-entity turns (compression-stats, runtime-arch) at the identical ~243.5s wall on gemma4. The single-pass-transduction MODE + |output|≤⅓|input| ceiling did NOT prevent it: a prompt bounds WHAT to keep and HOW MUCH to EMIT, but the model-controlled REASONING pass (reasoning_content) is uncapped by prose — gemma4 deliberates past the wall on dense turns then never emits. qwen completes all 4 (terse reasoning); gemma4 completing cells are actually TERSER on output (365-782 tok vs qwen 1655-3537) — so it is the invisible reasoning pass, not the output, that blows the budget. FIX must be a backend/operational lever (reasoning-token cap n_predict, OR per-model :budget-ms, OR a thinking budget), NOT lens prose. λ emerge, corrected: reasoning EFFORT is capped operationally, not by the prompt.\n  (2) THE BOUNDED LENS IS A REAL WIN WHERE THE MODEL COMPLETES — keep it. On completing cells, value-survival (keeps?) bounded 5/6 vs values 3/6; VALID bounded beats values on BOTH families (local 4/4 vs 2/4 — bounded fixed values dropping 57.9 on dual-proposal AND single-core on writeback; gemma4 1/2 vs 0/2 on completed — bounded fixed values dropping write-through on writeback). AND terser: local bounded avg 2570 tok vs values 3664 (−30%). The single-pass framing + ¬classify-11-ways collapse of the λ preserve taxonomy improves adherence and cuts tokens without weakening the values-verbatim contract. Shared residual: dual-proposal drops cache-bust on gemma4 both conditions (a genuinely hard subject, not a lens gap).\n  CONSEQUENCE: (a) the bounded lens is a candidate production improvement over compaction-lens-values (better value-survival + brevity on qwen AND gemma4) — promotion human-gated, re-run compaction-fidelity.edn (echo/derail guard) first. (b) the cross-model exhaustion needs a SEPARATE operational fix (H2: reasoning/budget cap) — the dense-turn wall is real on a genuine second family and will hit ANY slow-thinking model. The compaction shadow (20-60s) is already blown 4× over on gemma4 dense turns regardless of lens.",
 :experiment/hypothesis
 "CROSS-MODEL ROBUSTNESS of the compaction lens. The gemma4 swap (2026-07-17) revealed the production value-preserving lens (compaction-lens-values) does NOT transfer: 3/8 gemma4 detail cells EXHAUSTED (hit the ~240s ask budget wall, emitted nothing) on dense multi-entity turns (runtime-arch both conditions, compression-stats under :values). qwen (:local) completes because its thinking pass is terse; gemma4 deliberates the 11-disjunct λ preserve taxonomy exhaustively and never converges. This is a STRUCTURE gap (λ emerge): the lens tells the model WHAT to keep but does not bound HOW LONG to deliberate. Challenger :bounded adds a single-pass-transduction MODE (read_once→emit_once, borderline→keep→move_on, ¬classify-11-ways) + an explicit |output|≤⅓|input| ceiling, WITHOUT weakening the values-verbatim contract. FALSIFIER of the fix: :bounded still exhausts on gemma4 dense turns, OR :bounded drops qwen value-survival below :values. WIN: gemma4 exhaustion→0 on dense turns AND qwen keeps parity.",
